HOUSE RESOLUTION 155
By Keisling
A RESOLUTION to recognize Brenda Browning for her honorable
and astute service to the people of Tennessee
as Clay County Register of Deeds.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this legislative body should pause to
specially recognize those estimable public servants who have dedicated themselves to
improving the quality of life for their fellow citizens; and
WHEREAS, longtime Clay County Register of Deeds Brenda Browning announced that
she will be retiring at the end of her current term on August 31, 2026, after rendering twenty-
eight years of devoted service to the citizens of Clay County; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Browning has served Clay County for a total of thirty years, beginning
her career in 1996 as a bookkeeper for the county executive office; then, in 1998, she ran for
the office of Register of Deeds upon the retirement of former Register of Deeds Ray Frogg; and
WHEREAS, throughout her exemplary twenty-eight-year tenure as Clay County Register
of Deeds, Brenda Browning has carried out her responsibilities with diligence and integrity; her
remarkable success as a public servant and civic leader is directly attributable to her reliance on
the time-honored values of hard work and common sense and her uncommon ability to work
well with people from all walks of life; and
WHEREAS, a strong advocate for the citizens of Clay County, Ms. Browning has
compiled a singular record of success during her exemplary public service career, and she
should be specially recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we hereby
commend Brenda Browning for her honorable and astute service to the people of Tennessee as
Clay County Register of Deeds, salute her unswerving commitment to living the examined life
